{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":964,"text":"When I was 11,"},{"time":2404,"text":"I remember waking up one morning to the sound of joy in my house."},{"time":6966,"text":"My father was listening to BBC News"},{"time":9437,"text":"on his small, gray radio."},{"time":13611,"text":"There was a big smile on his face which was unusual then,"},{"time":16487,"text":"because the news mostly depressed him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":20458,"text":"\"The Taliban are gone!\" my father shouted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25343,"text":"I didn't know what it meant,"},{"time":27931,"text":"but I could see that my father was very, very happy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":33117,"text":"\"You can go to a real school now,\" he said."}]},{"cues":[{"time":41628,"text":"A morning that I will never forget."},{"time":46797,"text":"A real school."},{"time":51965,"text":"You see, I was six when the Taliban took over Afghanistan"},{"time":55073,"text":"and made it illegal for girls to go to school."},{"time":58596,"text":"So for the next five years, I dressed as a boy"},{"time":61704,"text":"to escort my older sister, who was no longer allowed"},{"time":64215,"text":"to be outside alone, to a secret school."},{"time":69629,"text":"It was the only way we both could be educated."},{"time":74254,"text":"Each day, we took a different route"},{"time":77488,"text":"so that no one would suspect where we were going."},{"time":81511,"text":"We would cover our books in grocery bags"},{"time":83705,"text":"so it would seem we were just out shopping."},{"time":89841,"text":"The school was in a house,"},{"time":92217,"text":"more than 100 of us packed in one small living room."},{"time":97880,"text":"It was cozy in winter but extremely hot in summer."},{"time":103730,"text":"We all knew we were risking our lives --"},{"time":106251,"text":"the teacher, the students and our parents."},{"time":110605,"text":"From time to time, the school would suddenly be canceled"},{"time":112978,"text":"for a week because Taliban were suspicious."},{"time":116894,"text":"We always wondered what they knew about us."},{"time":119674,"text":"Were we being followed?"},{"time":122706,"text":"Do they know where we live?"},{"time":126238,"text":"We were scared,"},{"time":128896,"text":"but still, school was where we wanted to be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":135822,"text":"I was very lucky to grow up in a family"},{"time":139562,"text":"where education was prized and daughters were treasured."},{"time":145809,"text":"My grandfather was an extraordinary man for his time."},{"time":150960,"text":"A total maverick from a remote province of Afghanistan,"},{"time":154439,"text":"he insisted that his daughter, my mom,"},{"time":157935,"text":"go to school, and for that he was disowned by his father."},{"time":164348,"text":"But my educated mother became a teacher."},{"time":167858,"text":"There she is."},{"time":170884,"text":"She retired two years ago, only to turn our house"},{"time":173551,"text":"into a school for girls and women in our neighborhood."},{"time":178929,"text":"And my father -- that's him --"},{"time":183317,"text":"he was the first ever in his family to receive an education."},{"time":190218,"text":"There was no question that his children"},{"time":192327,"text":"would receive an education, including his daughters,"},{"time":197416,"text":"despite the Taliban, despite the risks."},{"time":201836,"text":"To him, there was greater risk in not educating his children."},{"time":210182,"text":"During Taliban years, I remember"},{"time":213310,"text":"there were times I would get so frustrated by our life"},{"time":218403,"text":"and always being scared and not seeing a future."},{"time":222355,"text":"I would want to quit,"},{"time":225409,"text":"but my father,"},{"time":228545,"text":"he would say,"},{"time":231054,"text":"\"Listen, my daughter,"},{"time":233159,"text":"you can lose everything you own in your life."},{"time":236475,"text":"Your money can be stolen. You can be forced to leave your home during a war."},{"time":240680,"text":"But the one thing that will always remain with you"},{"time":243461,"text":"is what is here,"},{"time":246769,"text":"and if we have to sell our blood to pay your school fees,"},{"time":251685,"text":"we will."},{"time":254906,"text":"So do you still not want to continue?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":259988,"text":"Today I am 22."},{"time":263116,"text":"I was raised in a country that has been destroyed"},{"time":265886,"text":"by decades of war."},{"time":269056,"text":"Fewer than six percent of women my age have made it beyond high school,"},{"time":274197,"text":"and had my family not been so committed to my education,"},{"time":276662,"text":"I would be one of them."},{"time":279266,"text":"Instead, I stand here a proud graduate of Middlebury College."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284581,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":294594,"text":"When I returned to Afghanistan, my grandfather,"},{"time":297542,"text":"the one exiled from his home for daring to educate his daughters,"},{"time":302121,"text":"was among the first to congratulate me."},{"time":305615,"text":"He not only brags about my college degree,"},{"time":308245,"text":"but also that I was the first woman,"},{"time":310454,"text":"and that I am the first woman"},{"time":312176,"text":"to drive him through the streets of Kabul."}]},{"cues":[{"time":315678,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":321040,"text":"My family believes in me."},{"time":323689,"text":"I dream big, but my family dreams even bigger for me."},{"time":328639,"text":"That's why I am a global ambassador for 10x10,"},{"time":333106,"text":"a global campaign to educate women."},{"time":335870,"text":"That's why I cofounded SOLA,"},{"time":338449,"text":"the first and perhaps only boarding school"},{"time":340916,"text":"for girls in Afghanistan,"},{"time":342645,"text":"a country where it's still risky for girls to go to school."},{"time":348282,"text":"The exciting thing is that I see students at my school"},{"time":352047,"text":"with ambition grabbing at opportunity."},{"time":357675,"text":"And I see their parents and their fathers"},{"time":360602,"text":"who, like my own, advocate for them,"},{"time":365180,"text":"despite and even in the face of daunting opposition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":374112,"text":"Like Ahmed. That's not his real name,"},{"time":376818,"text":"and I cannot show you his face,"},{"time":379446,"text":"but Ahmed is the father of one of my students."},{"time":383091,"text":"Less than a month ago, he and his daughter"},{"time":386927,"text":"were on their way from SOLA to their village,"},{"time":390261,"text":"and they literally missed being killed"},{"time":396754,"text":"by a roadside bomb by minutes."},{"time":401536,"text":"As he arrived home, the phone rang,"},{"time":404939,"text":"a voice warning him"},{"time":407634,"text":"that if he sent his daughter back to school,"},{"time":411029,"text":"they would try again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413806,"text":"\"Kill me now, if you wish,\" he said,"},{"time":417708,"text":"\"but I will not ruin my daughter's future"},{"time":421602,"text":"because of your old and backward ideas.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":426434,"text":"What I've come to realize about Afghanistan,"},{"time":428803,"text":"and this is something that is often dismissed in the West,"},{"time":432323,"text":"that behind most of us who succeed"},{"time":435546,"text":"is a father who recognizes the value in his daughter"},{"time":442909,"text":"and who sees that her success is his success."},{"time":447536,"text":"It's not to say that our mothers aren't key in our success."},{"time":451474,"text":"In fact, they're often the initial and convincing negotiators"},{"time":456010,"text":"of a bright future for their daughters,"},{"time":459350,"text":"but in the context of a society like in Afghanistan,"},{"time":462761,"text":"we must have the support of men."},{"time":466181,"text":"Under the Taliban, girls who went to school"},{"time":469731,"text":"numbered in the hundreds --"},{"time":471523,"text":"remember, it was illegal."},{"time":473861,"text":"But today, more than three million girls are in school in Afghanistan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":479353,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":486600,"text":"Afghanistan looks so different from here in America."},{"time":492751,"text":"I find that Americans see the fragility in changes."},{"time":497723,"text":"I fear that these changes will not last"},{"time":500773,"text":"much beyond the U.S. troops' withdrawal."},{"time":505265,"text":"But when I am back in Afghanistan,"},{"time":508918,"text":"when I see the students in my school"},{"time":513703,"text":"and their parents who advocate for them,"},{"time":516343,"text":"who encourage them, I see a promising future"},{"time":520810,"text":"and lasting change."},{"time":524110,"text":"To me, Afghanistan is a country of hope and boundless possibilities,"},{"time":532577,"text":"and every single day"},{"time":535989,"text":"the girls of SOLA remind me of that."},{"time":539397,"text":"Like me, they are dreaming big."}]},{"cues":[{"time":542604,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":544315,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}